"'''Boombastic'''" is the second single released by [[Shaggy (musician)|Shaggy]] from his album ''[[Boombastic]]''. Released in 1995, it achieved huge success in many countries, including Ireland, UK, Sweden, New Zealand and Australia where it topped the singles charts.

==Song information==
It spent a week at number one on the [[United States|U.S.]] ''Billboard'' [[Rhythm and Blues|R&B]] [[record chart|chart]], and a similar stint atop the [[UK Singles Chart]]. It also reached number three on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]. A remix featuring [[Shaun Pizzonia|Sting International]] features a sample of [[Marvin Gaye]]'s "[[Let's Get It On]]." The latter is featured on some versions of the album as a bonus track. The single was released in the UK under [[12"]] and [[CD single]] formats. 

Boombastic gained popularity after being featured in a popular [[Levi's]] television commercial.<ref>{{cite book |first=Alex P. |last=King |title=Hit-parade <U+2014> 20 ans de tubes |publisher=Pascal |year=2004 |place=Paris |page=349 |language=French |isbn=2-35019-009-9}}</ref>

The song was featured in the films ''[[Barnyard (film)|Barnyard]]'', ''[[Mr. Bean's Holiday]]'', and ''[[George of the Jungle (film)|George of the Jungle]]''.

